g.text: Read a tab separated csv file
First filter out genes with very low read counts. Then perform
differential gene expression with the DESeq node. The CSV
Reader should read the annotation matrix in tabular format. The
CSV writer writes the deseq results to a csv file.
First performs the quality control with FastQC, followed by trimming and clipping with the RawReadManipulator and quality control again
with FastQC afterwards. Filtered read data is mapped to the reference transcriptome with bowtie2 and quantified with the Java Snippet.
The Java snippet performs several samtools calls and performs read quantification using idxstats. The R snippet combines separate read
count files into one table to use for differential gene expression analysis.
